1 insp ecting, estimating, protecting, repairing, restoring, or
2 replacing the property or mitigating against further damage to the
3 property; and
4 2. "Person" means:
5 a. a natural person,
6 b. any type or form of corporation, company, partnership,
7 proprietorship, association, or other legal entity,
8 and
9 c. a government, governmental subdivision or agency, or
10 other governmental body.
11 B. 1. A person shall not solicit or accept an assignment, in
12 whole or in part, of any post-loss insurance benefit for property
13 damage under an auto collision or comprehensive policy, residential
14 property insurance policy, or commercial property insurance policy.
15 An assignment agreement is against public policy and is null and
16 void, and any contract entered in violation of this section shall be
17 void and unenforceable.
18 2. The provisions of paragraph 1 of this subsection do not
19 apply to any of the following:
20 a. an assignment, transfer, pledge, or conveyance granted
21 to a federally insured financial institution,
22 mortgagee, or a subsequent purchaser of the property,
23 or
24
